---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Russia.md"
  description="Why this fork exists, what it covers, and how to extend it into a larger Russia-focused knowledge base."
>
  <main class="page">
    <section class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Why this project exists</h1>
      <p>
        `Russia.md` is a fork of the open-source [`taiwan-md`](https://github.com/frank890417/taiwan-md)
        project, rebuilt as a starter knowledge base about Russia. The intent is to preserve the useful
        structure of the original project while replacing country-specific assumptions, category descriptions,
        navigation, and starter content.
      </p>
      <p>
        This version is a foundation, not a finished encyclopedia. It keeps the site architecture and the
        category-driven reading model, then seeds each section with one Russia-focused article so contributors
        can expand it without inheriting Taiwan-specific narrative or metadata.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="wrap grid">
      <article>
        <h2>What’s included</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>A rewritten landing page and site shell</li>
          <li>Russia-specific category descriptions</li>
          <li>Starter essays across 12 categories</li>
          <li>A practical <a href="/SKILLS.md">SKILLS.md</a> for LLM-agent integrations</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>What still needs work</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>More articles per category</li>
          <li>Russia-specific data visualizations instead of inherited Taiwan placeholders</li>
          <li>Custom domain, analytics, and deployment configuration</li>
          <li>Deeper editorial policy and sourcing standards</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="wrap">
      <h2>Editorial direction</h2>
      <p>
        The repo should aim for concise, cited, non-touristic writing. Strong versions of this project explain
        why a topic matters, where it sits in the broader Russian context, and what an informed reader should
        understand next.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .wrap {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: #64748b;
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  p, li {
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #334155;
  }
</style>
